Iceland Lenders Write Off $2.8 Billion in Debt for 41 Companies

-- B y   O m a r   R .   V a l d i m a r s s o n
-- 
2011-09-23T11:27:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/iceland-lenders-write-off-2-8-billion-in-debt-for-41-companies.html
Icelandic banks and other financial
companies wrote off 336 billion kronur ($2.8 billion) of debt
from 41 companies from mid-December to June 30, the  Economy
Ministry  said.  Seven real estate and holding companies were forgiven 170
billion kronur in debt, while 88.5 billion kronur was written
off for 13 retail companies, according to a report from the
Reykjavik-based ministry. A total of 26.6 billion kronur was
forgiven for four building contractors, among other write-offs.  Another nine companies, which owed a combined 91.5 billion,
had their debt converted to equity, according to the  report .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Omar R. Valdimarsson in Reykjavik 
